      <hedline>
        <hl1>DiMassimo Appoints 5 Partners</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Allison Fass</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Fass, Allison</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>DiMassimo Brand Advertising names five executives as partners: Melissa Brooks, Leo Goldstein, Carla Hall, Jonathan Lee and Doug Ray (Advertising column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>DiMassimo Brand Advertising in New York has named five executives as partners. Each will be given an equal, undisclosed minority stake in the agency and take on the additional title of managing partner. They are: Melissa Brooks, 31, director for brand management; Lee Goldstein, 28, director for business development; Carla Hall, 32, executive producer; Jonathan Lee, 30, director for brand planning; and Doug Ray, 30, director for brand media and new media.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>DiMassimo Brand Advertising in New York has named five executives as partners. Each will be given an equal, undisclosed minority stake in the agency and take on the additional title of managing partner. They are: Melissa Brooks, 31, director for brand management; Lee Goldstein, 28, director for business development; Carla Hall, 32, executive producer; Jonathan Lee, 30, director for brand planning; and Doug Ray, 30, director for brand media and new media.</p>
